4:
You've been randomly selected for 
a field evaluation.
11:
The Guild contracts specialists—such 
as myself—to routinely review the 
performance of adventurers, and 
ensure they are fit to handle Guild 
quests.
12:
I will be accompanying you on your 
quest today. You will be evaluated on 
your professionalism, efficiency, and 
conduct.
16:
My name is Jake. I'm looking forward 
to working with you.
23:
It's only a routine check. Think of it as 
a chance for us to show the guild what 
we're capable of.
26:
That's the spirit! It sounds scarier than 
it is—hardly anyone fails the 
evaluation. Just relax and do your 
quest like normal.
27:
Jake can be a bit intimidating at first, 
but he's another adventurer just like 
you guys.
30:
While I appreciate the attempt to 
lighten the mood, please make no 
mistakes.
31:
I am a professional, and my report 
WILL be forwarded to the Guild proper. 
I expect full compliance with Guild 
regulations—from them and you.
39:
We've arrived at the orphanage, so 
I now will begin my evaluation. Please 
be aware I am prohibited from 
assisting you in any way. You may 
begin.
43:
Let's see... Quest selection: assisting 
a local orphanage. Selection indicates 
compassion and a sense of 
responsibility to the local community.
47:
Oh! Are you all right?
You ought to look where you're going, 
young man!
53: Shhh. Jake is stern, but he isn't angry.
59:
Of course. I apologize for scaring you. 
Running blindly can be very 
dangerous—I wouldn't want you to get 
hurt now, okay?
70:
I obstructed the assessees' duties! I... 
I b-broke... the rules...
74:
My contract strictly prohibits me from 
aiding or inhibiting adventurers during 
evaluations! What have I done?! I'm so 
sorry, I... I can't believe it...
79:
We haven't even met the quest-giver 
yet, so can't the evaluation start then?
88:
I broke the rules. I-I should've just kept 
my mouth shut...
94:
Why? You were trying to help the child, 
not us.
99:
While I understand your sentiment, 
rules exist for a reason—the spirit of 
the law is more important than the 
letter.
100:
The children don't know or care that 
you're examining us. If you stood 
around silently glaring at everyone, it 
would scare them and obstruct our 
work.
109:
Light's right, Jake! The kid's okay, so no 
harm, no foul.
117:
Whew, all done! I'd say we did pretty 
well!
120:
The matron was very pleased with our 
work. With this, I believe it's safe to say 
we'll pass our evaluation.
128:
Swimmingly. Just between us, you're 
the best party I've ever reviewed.
132: Jake?! Wait, why are you here?!
134:
Your professionalism and teamwork 
deeply impressed me. I wanted to 
speak with you about it personally—off 
the clock.
138:
I'd just about caught up when there 
was a flash and... where are we?
143:
Ho-hold on, this ABSOLUTELY can't go 
in the report!
146:
The field evaluation is just that—an 
assessment of whether or not you 
perform well on quests.
151:
Please be assured, it's not 
a background check, and I've already 
finished my report anyhow.
155:
Besides, I'm a third-party specialist 
contracted by the Guild. Divulging 
assessees' personal information would 
VERY much violate the rules on 
impartiality and privacy.
159:
That's reassuring to hear. We ask that 
you keep anything you see here to 
yourself.
167:
Yeah, feel free to swing by and say hi 
whenever!
171: Thank you. It would be my pleasure.
